97, number 34 (April 8-14, 2020) (miamitimesonline.com ; viewed September 25, 2025)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-18T06:33:12.414Z", "group": ["catalog-split-07", "catalog", "ndnp/newspapers", "main-catalog-split-07", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2025203405/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["dade county", "floride", "miami", "united states", "florida", "dade"], "number": ["online resource", "2025203405", "3069-6631", "1287811754", "2026-06-17t10:47:10.200000", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["catalog", "the miami times (miami, fla.) 1923-current", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 85.537094, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["catalog", "usnd"], "subject": ["dade", "newspapers", "miami-dade county", "miami-dade county (fla.)", "african american", "journaux", "miami (fla.)", "floride", "miami", "united states", "florida", "noirs am\u00e9ricains", "african americans"], "timestamp": "2026-06-18T06:46:53.438Z", "title": "The Miami times", "type": ["newspaper"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2025203405/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83004231/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83004231", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/0ef0d218-c74b-5698-8771-9e6f7907c236"], "batch": ["fu_armadillo_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1923", "description": ["Weekly Began in 1923. \"Florida's favorite Colored weekly.\" \"Tempora mutantur et nos mutamur in illis.\" Editor: H.F. Sigismund Reeves, <Jan. 6, 1967-Dec. 27, 1968>. Also issued on microfilm from the University of Florida, and the Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Also issued by subscription via the World Wide Web. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America onlin